<paragraph id="8BF18648FFC9FF89FF24982E38A9994E" blockId="24.[164,779,320,373]" pageId="24" pageNumber="350">
<emphasis id="B93A5A5AFFC9FF89FF24982E3B52996E" box="[164,290,320,341]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="350">Etymology:</emphasis>
The name 
<taxonomicName id="4C4EFDCBFFC9FF89FE25982E3841996E" authorityName="Prathapan &amp; Viraktamath" authorityYear="2009" box="[421,561,320,341]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Tegyrius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="350" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigrotibialis">
<emphasis id="B93A5A5AFFC9FF89FE25982E3841996E" box="[421,561,320,341]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="350">nigrotibialis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
refers to the black colour of the beetle, and the modified mesotibia.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF18648FFC9FF89FF2498F23BE19A35" blockId="24.[164,779,412,526]" pageId="24" pageNumber="350">
<emphasis id="B93A5A5AFFC9FF89FF2498F2387B998A" box="[164,523,412,434]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="350">
Remarks: 
<taxonomicName id="4C4EFDCBFFC9FF89FE9798F3387B998A" authority="Prathapan &amp; Viraktamath, 2009" authorityName="Prathapan &amp; Viraktamath" authorityYear="2009" box="[279,523,412,434]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Tegyrius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="350" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigrotibialis" status="sp. nov.">Tegyrius nigrotibialis</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A209E721FFC9FF89FD9398F338199989" box="[531,617,413,434]" pageId="24" pageNumber="350" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
can be distinguished from all other black species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C4EFDCBFFC9FF89FDDD98D538CD99EB" authorityName="Jacoby" authorityYear="1887" box="[605,701,443,464]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Tegyrius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="350" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B93A5A5AFFC9FF89FDDD98D538CD99EB" box="[605,701,443,464]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="350">Tegyrius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the sexually dimorphic mesotibia, as well as by the apically bifid aedeagus.
</paragraph>
